I love this place. Every time I go I always get the Mediterranean crepes because they are heavenly. My out-of-town friend really loved her chicken wrap. Its really a cute place with friendly staff. Oh, the strawberry cream pastry I took home was divine.
Excellent food and ambiance! Friendly staff.
Customer Service is exceptional. The staff are wonderful.

They deserve all the praise I can give. My husband is very physically disabled and we don't get out much, but we wanted to try the crepes and have a little breakfast date. Not only were they accessible, they were INCREDIBLY WELCOMING and so sweet. We had the lemon strawberry crepe and the Nutella banana waffle. Both were AMAZING. Their coffee and smoothies are good too! We also tried some macaroons and a raspberry eclair, all of which was delicious. Highly recommend this cute little cafe for anyone passing by or local. It was worth the 30 minute drive.
really good spot. I had the chicken chipotle on croissant and coffee. ☕️

The staff was very friendly and helpful. It didn't take long for us to get our food. Thank you for being a part of Toast. My veggie omelet was piping hot and good but next time I hope I can switch to a different cheese. At off times it's a great place to meet friends. Indoor and outdoor seating. It was quite chilly for me but I seemed to be the only one affected by it.

I recently had their PBC (Peanutbutter Crepe) and it was so delicious and I was able to add strawberries which made the crepe all the more irresistible.
The make your own crepes is a great concept!
Cappuccino was decadent with perfect amount of foam.
If I lived closer I would come here everyday and get happily fat.
exceptional customer service from manager Haile !⭐️the cakes are absolutely delicious - will definitely order cake again

I love Patisserie Cafe and the staff that runs it!

The food is all made from scratch, and cooked correctly. Never too salty, or bland, or burnt or undercooked, just consistent and fantastic!

I'm a quiche snob; I eat them at any place that sells them. These are the best around, by far. The crust is buttery and perfect - not soggy, and not crispy.

They also have great coffee and desserts, and their lunch menu is exceptional.

I had a positive experience with the food, which was excellent. However, I encountered a significant issue with the service at the pickup counter. On multiple occasions, I found myself waiting for nearly 10 minutes without any acknowledgment from the staff. While they were busy with other tasks, such as cleaning silverware and attending to other customers, it was disheartening to feel overlooked.
It would be beneficial for management to provide additional training to the staff to ensure they remain attentive to customers at the pickup counter, especially when orders are marked as ready for pickup. I ordered from Patisserie Cafe for my Galentines Day Brunch. The Brunch was on a Sunday (they are closed Sundays), so I picked up my catering order Saturday afternoon. I ordered the bacon and cheese quiche, cheesy potatoes and the Southwest salad. Paola was nice enough to personally email me the reheating instructions for the quiche and potatoes. The staff also packed all the salad ingredients individually so I could put the salad together the next day. The food reheated perfectly and it all tasted AMAZING! The customer service was top notch. I will definitely be ordering from them again!

Cute place and lovely staff but if you’re going to change up an iconic item (huevos rancheros) you should give a heads up on your menu. Stacked tortilla, beans, tortilla, ham, eggs (not done over easy like I asked) and then cheddar cheese (when the waitress asked if I wanted my eggs scrambled I was alerted so I specifically said normal HR is with eggs over easy, salsa and cotijo cheese and was told yes they had everything on it!) Disappointing. Oh, and on top of that I asked for a side of bacon (b/c I didn’t know the ham was on there) and they piled it on w the ham. And all of that with a coffee and breakfast for my husband for a mere $40!
Gluten-free options are available. The best gluten-free almond cookies. They also have gluten-free brownies. Great food and excellent service. Highly recommend.

I have been to Patisserie Cafe twice and both times have been this week! First, I had a ham and cheese omelette for breakfast which was very tasty. I substituted fruit for potatoes. I chose the wheat toast. This order was for carry out.
The next day a friend and I had lunch there. I chose the salad with grilled chicken. I asked to substitute ranch dressing rather than the dressing they usually have with it. I got the one that came with it but when I asked for ranch dressing the server apologized and got the ranch quickly even though it was the lunch rush. I tried both dressings. The pastries and baked goods are crafted with care and precision—each bite bursts with flavor and freshness. I would have only given 1 start because of the breakfast sandwiches,but gave 2 since they tried to please the customer. I initially ordered a sausage,egg,and cheese sandwich on a croissant with their "supposedly" good creamy cheese potatoes. The sausage was chirizo...too spicy for the sandwich and I ordered it with no jalapenos...it came with jalapeños on it. Potatoes were kinda slimy / mush-ee with their style of a creamy cheese mixer. Sent it back. In its place I got the bacon,egg, and cheese on toasted white bread. Bread was barely toasted so I removed the ingredients from the bread and ate them with a fork.  The bacon was tough...appears they use bacon bits mixed in with the scrambled egg vs freshly cooked bacon for the sandwich. Both sandwiches had so much cheese that almost every bite was stringy. This order had fried potatoes which were under cooked.
Their pastries look good but did not try any.
Nice people, friendly, but definitely missed the target twice on their breakfast sandwiches.
Did I mention it was $16 (+) for the sandwich, potatoe, and a coke? Seemed a bit high.
I do not recommend this place based on the above.
